# Local env
.env

# OS
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Editors
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp

# Python (used by any lab tooling)
__pycache__/
*.pyc
.venv/
venv/
.pytest_cache/

# Certificates and security
**/certificates/
**/keystore/

# Runtime configuration (environment-specific). NOTE: the LOCAL gateway's
# copies under services/config/ are deliberately tracked (a fresh clone needs
# the `local` collection manifest on disk or first boot FAULTs); tracked files
# override these patterns, and the skip-worktree hook hides their churn.
# .dockerignore keeps them out of the image either way.
**/config/local
**/config/resources/local

# The gateway-owned INTERNAL identity: the default user source (users.json
# holds the admin password hash!), its identity provider, and the OPC-UA
# module's user source belong to ONE gateway. Committing them ships your
# local gateway's admin credentials to every gateway you deploy to — and
# locks everyone out of dev/prod. Identity resources you configure yourself
# (a database or AD user source, a SAML/OIDC identity provider) hold no
# password data and ARE tracked and deployed like any other config.
**/config/resources/core/ignition/user-source/default/
**/config/resources/core/ignition/user-source/opcua-module/
**/config/resources/core/ignition/identity-provider/default/

# Ignition operational state — never commit these (see docs/ignition-file-structure.md)
# These live inside the gateway's data/ directory at runtime; we mount them as a named
# volume so they don't pollute the bind-mounted projects/ and services/ paths.
**/.resources/
**/migration-log-*.md
**/jar-cache/
**/datacache/
**/autobackup/
**/config/ignition/tags/*.idb
**/themes.digest.json
**/fonts.digest.json
**/icons.digest.json

# Data-root operational state (db/ — the internal SQLite DB incl. the user store —
# jar-cache/, metricsdb/, var/) lives in the gateways' named volumes and never
# appears in this repo's tree, so it needs no patterns here.